    <textAnnotation id="sid-59BBC2DD-8C4E-40AA-B2EB-9E94901D9C70" signavio:alignment="left">
      <extensionElements>
        <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000" />
        <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="11.0" italic="" ref="text-left" />
        <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="11.0" italic="" ref="text-right" />
      </extensionElements>
      <text>We assume that a prescription includes many details such as the needed medications, dosage, patient information, etc.</text>
    </textAnnotation>
    <textAnnotation id="sid-02037E7D-9D93-4CBB-9BE6-7CD2D382FE89" signavio:alignment="left">
      <extensionElements>
        <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000" />
        <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="11.0" italic="" ref="text-left" />
        <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="11.0" italic="" ref="text-right" />
      </extensionElements>
      <text>It can be treated as an independent subprocess that handles order cancellations across multiple pharmacy processes.</text>
    </textAnnotation>
